  "content": [
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "[image: Bga studio small.jpg]"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "Board Game Arena Studio is a platform to build online board game adaptations using the Board Game Arena platform."
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "BGA Studio website: https://studio.boardgamearena.com"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "Why, how, what... to start discovering BGA Studio, we prepared 5 \"powerpoint\" presentations for you:"
    },
    {
      "type": "list",
      "ordered": false,
      "items": [
        {
          "text": "5 reasons why you should use BGA Studio for your online board game (or ‎Download as PDF )",
          "nested": null
        },
        {
          "text": "The 8 steps to create a board game on Board Game Arena (or Download as PDF )",
          "nested": null
        },
        {
          "text": "The BGA Framework at a glance (or Download as PDF )",
          "nested": null
        },
        {
          "text": "Focus on BGA game state machine (or Download as PDF )",
          "nested": null
        },
        {
          "text": "BGA developers guidelines (or ‎Download as PDF )",
          "nested": null
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "Please see this page: How to join BGA developer team?"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "If you didn't already, check the presentations at the top of this page to get the basics."
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "After that, we strongly advise you to take one of these game creation tutorials:"
    },
    {
      "type": "list",
      "ordered": false,
      "items": [
        {
          "text": "Tutorial reversi ( recommended , closest to the actual BGA implementation and maintained by the BGA team) - an abstract strategy game played on an 8×8 uncheckered board for 2 players",
          "nested": null
        },
        {
          "text": "Tutorial hearts - a card game for 4 players",
          "nested": null
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "Then start editing files and see what happens! ;)"
    },
    {
      "type": "list",
      "ordered": false,
      "items": [
        {
          "text": "Create a game in BGA Studio: Complete Walkthrough",
          "nested": null
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "If you have any questions, please check out the Studio FAQ or Contact BGA Studio ."
    },
    {
      "type": "code",
      "language": null,
      "text": " \"Category:Studio\" white rabbit "
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "That is if you want to search for white rabbit"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "This part of the documentation focuses on the development framework itself: functions and methods available to build your game."
    },
    {
      "type": "list",
      "ordered": false,
      "items": [
        {
          "text": "Main game logic: Game.php",
          "nested": null
        },
        {
          "text": "Your game state classes: States directory",
          "nested": null
        },
        {
          "text": "Game database model: dbmodel.sql",
          "nested": null
        },
        {
          "text": "Game material description: material.inc.php",
          "nested": null
        },
        {
          "text": "Game statistics: stats.json",
          "nested": null
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "list",
      "ordered": false,
      "items": [
        {
          "text": "Game interface logic: Game.js",
          "nested": null
        },
        {
          "text": "Game art: img directory",
          "nested": null
        },
        {
          "text": "Game interface stylesheet: yourgamename.css",
          "nested": null
        },
        {
          "text": "Game layout: view and template: yourgamename.view.php and yourgamename_yourgamename.tpl",
          "nested": null
        },
        {
          "text": "Your game mobile version",
          "nested": null
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "list",
      "ordered": false,
      "items": [
        {
          "text": "Translations (how to make your game translatable)",
          "nested": null
        },
        {
          "text": "Game Options and Preferences",
          "nested": null
        },
        {
          "text": "Game meta-information: gameinfos.jsonc",
          "nested": null
        },
        {
          "text": "Game replay",
          "nested": null
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "Game components are useful tools you can use in your game adaptations."
    },
    {
      "type": "list",
      "ordered": false,
      "items": [
        {
          "text": "Counter : a JS component to manage a counter that can increase/decrease (ex: player's score).",
          "nested": null
        },
        {
          "text": "Scrollmap : a JS component to manage a scrollable game area (useful when the game area can be infinite. Examples:  Saboteur or Takenoko games).",
          "nested": null
        },
        {
          "text": "Stock : a JS component to manage and display a set of game elements displayed at a position.",
          "nested": null
        },
        {
          "text": "Zone : a JS component to manage a zone of the board where several game elements can come and leave, but should be well displayed together (See for example: token's places at Can't Stop).",
          "nested": null
        },
        {
          "text": "Draggable : a JS component to manage drag'n'drop actions.",
          "nested": null
        },
        {
          "text": "ExpandableSection : a JS component to manage a rectangular block of HTML than can be displayed/hidden.",
          "nested": null
        },
        {
          "text": "Anti-Stock : Code snippets in vanilla JS/HTML5 to do what stock does (that is if you cannot beat Stock into submission)",
          "nested": null
        },
        {
          "text": "bga-animations : a JS component for animations.",
          "nested": null
        },
        {
          "text": "bga-cards : a JS component for cards.",
          "nested": null
        },
        {
          "text": "bga-dice : a JS component for dice.",
          "nested": null
        },
        {
          "text": "bga-autofit : a JS component to make text fit on a fixed size div.",
          "nested": null
        },
        {
          "text": "bga-score-sheet : a JS component to help you display an animated score sheet at the end of the game.",
          "nested": null
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "PHP:"
    },
    {
      "type": "list",
      "ordered": false,
      "items": [
        {
          "text": "Deck : a PHP component to manage cards (deck, hands, picking cards, moving cards, shuffle deck, ...)",
          "nested": null
        },
        {
          "text": "PlayerCounter and TableCounter : php component to manager counters",
          "nested": null
        }
      ]
    },
